main event: Photographic slides showing several light spots observed over Dallas-Fort Worth, Texas on 19 June 1963.
interesting points: Sixteen slides were taken from an amusement park known as 'Big Dipper',Photos showed several light spots that were moving with the clouds, The analysis suggested the light spots were not physical objects but photographic effects, Similar sightings were reported around the same date, The slides were returned for further analysis to Project Blue Book.
sighted object: several light spots in the sky
witness description: individuals observing from a stationary vehicle
